name: Darker Github - 50 shades of blue
description: This is a theme made for GitHub. It is made darker, since i personally don't like the white pages from GitHub. They burn my eyes! Tried to keep as close as the official design from GitHub as possible, while making most darker / "blueish". The more blueish side instead of full dark, is because i personally like a full Deep dark theme, because for some reason it is missing something in my opion.
additional_info:
Just install the theme with stylus, as easy as clicking on add style and everything should be done. I've tried to make this theme to support all sites that include GitHub in some sort. 

Updates:

Since I'm not completely finished yet, i will try to fix most broken things and update (probably) a lot. Later on i will also comment more and organize everything better, so it's easier for other people to adapt if needed and make it easier to change the color scheme. It will be later available on GitHub as well, to fork or edit together.

Feedback:

I would like to appreciate some feedback, bugs and other helpful information, to make this theme better. I'll try to consider all possible feedback and make changes when appropriate. 

 - Of course it was impossible for me to test all buttons, hover, links and sites myself, any feedback (even the smallest detail) are welcome.  

Notice:

This is my first theme i made for userstyles.org and stylus. So please be gentle with feedback. Besides being gentle, be honest!

Together we can make a nice looking word wide web - without having our eyes burned. Starting with GitHub.

Made by Ch3c0.
